### 🟢 Level 8 ➔ Level 9
* **Objective:** Isolate the single non-repeating line of text from a massive file (`data.txt`) filled with duplicate entries.
* **Core Commands:** ```bash
  sort data.txt | uniq -u
This level introduces the concept of I/O streaming pipelines using the pipe operator (|).

    The Pipe (|): Intercepts the standard output stream of the left-hand command and redirects it as the standard input stream for the right-hand command.

    The Sorting Prerequisite: The uniq binary can only identify duplicate adjacent lines. Therefore, running sort data.txt is required first to group all identical strings together sequentially.

    Unique Isolation (-u): Passing the sorted stream into uniq -u instructs the utility to discard all recurring groups completely, printing only the solitary string that appeared exactly once.

    Status: Complete ➔ [FLAG_CAPTURED]

