* **Objective:** Extract a human-readable password preceded by multiple equal signs (`=`) from a largely unreadable binary data file (`data.txt`).
* **Core Commands:** ```bash
  strings data.txt | grep "=="
Standard text processing tools like cat or raw grep fail or corrupt terminal visuals when applied directly to compiled binary files.

    The strings Utility: Scans non-text/binary files to isolate and extract sequential bytes representing human-readable characters, discarding machine code noise.

    Pipeline Stream Control: To filter effectively, data must flow from the general data generator to the specific pattern matcher (strings [file] | grep [pattern]). This ensures grep receives the clean text stream and isolates solely the password line.

